DESCRIPTION:The 2025-2027 Cycling Network Plan identified Davisville Ave i
 n Ward 12 Toronto—St. Paul's for road safety improvements. Proposals inc
 lude new protected bike lanes with concrete low walls along Davisville bet
 ween Yonge and Mount Pleasant Rd. Come.to the drop-in public consultation 
 to learn more. These projects don’t happen without public support. (http
 s://www.toronto.ca/community-people/get-involved/public-consultations/infr
 astructure-projects/improving-davisville-avenue/) Learn more and complete 
 the survey.\n\n(Rendering of proposed changes to Davisville including prot
 ected bike lanes. Image: City of Toronto)\nURL: https://www.cycleto.ca/pub
 lic_consultation_davisville
LOCATION:Greenwood College School\n443 Mount Pleasant Rd\nToronto ON M4S 2
 L8\nCA
URL:https://www.cycleto.ca/public_consultation_davisville
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Cycle Toronto Midtown Screening: Changing Lanes
DTSTART:20260422T230000Z
DTEND:20260423T003000Z
DTSTAMP:20260415T061646Z
UID:646eeb26-3315-5a6c-a511-54b601a70ed5
DESCRIPTION:Join Cycle Toronto Midtown on Earth Day for a group ride throu
 gh Mount Pleasant Cemetery followed by a screening of the critically accla
 imed documentary Changing Lanes.\n\nWhen: April 22\nRide: 5:30 p.m. at Mou
 nt Pleasant Cemetery\, South Entrance\nScreening: 7 p.m. at the York Schoo
 l\, Senior Campus (1320 Yonge St\, Toronto)\n\nAll are welcome on the ride
 \, but seating for Changing Lanes is limited. PWYC cash at venue ($10 reco
 mmended). RSVP to reserve your seat.\n\nChanging Lanes (2025): When a belo
 ved teacher is tragically killed in a hit-and-run crash in Greenpoint\, Br
 ooklyn\, a grassroots movement emerges to transform a notoriously dangerou
 s four-lane boulevard into a safer\, two-lane street with protected bike l
 anes. While many applaud the proposed road diet\, it also sparks a backlas
 h — led in part by a powerful local business owner. As government suppor
 t begins to waver\, neighbors unite to challenge entrenched interests and 
 fight for a safer Greenpoint.\nURL: https://www.cycleto.ca/cycle_toronto_m
 idtown_earth_day
LOCATION:York School\, Senior Campus\n1320 Yonge Street\nToronto ON M4T 3B
 2\nCA
URL:https://www.cycleto.ca/cycle_toronto_midtown_earth_day
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Public Consultation: Elmhurst
